Belka Calls for `Moderate' Polish Inflation Response on Weak Wage Pressure

-- B y   N a t h a n i e l   E s p i n o
-- 
2011-02-21T07:26:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/belka-calls-for-moderate-polish-inflation-response-on-weak-wage-pressure.html
  Poland ’s central bank should have a
“moderate” response to inflation as long as wage pressure
remains mild, central bank Governor Marek Belka said, according
to the PAP news agency.  The January decision to increase rates doesn’t
automatically mean a “cascade” of increases in coming months,
as external price shocks are “dissipating,” PAP quoted him as
saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nathaniel Espino at 
 nespino@bloomberg.net  